data.oai_dc:dc: Birds, Belize, Occurrence|Observation, Birds, Belize, Point Count

Point count data collected at the Toledo Institute for Development and Environment (TIDE) private land (Block 127) in southern Belize. Data was collected from January 2009 to February 2013.|The dataset was developed based on point count data collected by the Toledo Institute for Development and Environment. The dataset includes observational data of both resident and migrant species. Having data on birds in Belize will allow information to be generated on diversity, abundance, etc.|2,695 occurrences
